{"word":"θαμβέω","slug":"θαμβέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>θαμβέω</b></el> <el>(θαμβέω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:θάμβος'><el>θάμβος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to be astounded, amazed</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to be astonished at, marvel at</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>Causal, <i>to surprise</i>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>τεθαμβημένος</el> <i>astounded</i>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}